{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"language":"python","display_name":"Python 3","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.12.13","mimetype":"text/x-python","codemirror_mode":{"name":"ipython","version":3},"pygments_lexer":"ipython3","nbconvert_exporter":"python","file_extension":".py"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[],"dockerImageVersionId":28755,"isInternetEnabled":false,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# 🧠 Gemma 4 AI News Summarizer — Kaggle Training Notebook\n\n **Model**: `google/gemma-4` (12B via `kagglehub` — Kaggle-native loading)\n **Method**: QLoRA (4-bit quantisation + LoRA adapters)\n **Library**: TRL SFTTrainer + PEFT\n **Hardware**: Kaggle T4 x2 or P100 (16 GB VRAM)\n **Time**: ~60–120 min for 3 epochs on 500 examples (12B)\n\n ✅ Prerequisites (do these BEFORE running):\n 1. Go to https://www.kaggle.com/models/google/gemma-4\n 2. Click **\"Request Access\"** → **\"Verify via Kaggle Account\"** → Submit\n 3. Attach the model to this notebook: Add-ons → Models → search \"gemma-4\"\n 4. Enable GPU: Settings → Accelerator → GPU T4 x2","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 1. Install Dependencies\n\n> Run this cell first, then **restart the kernel** before continuing.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"\n# ─── Install required packages (restart kernel after running) ───────────────\n!pip install -q \\\n\"transformers>=4.40.0\" \\\n\"peft>=0.10.0\" \\\n\"trl>=0.8.6\" \\\n\"bitsandbytes>=0.43.0\" \\\n\"accelerate>=0.28.0\" \\\n\"datasets\" \\\n\"rouge_score\"\n!pip install --upgrade transformers","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 2. Imports & GPU Check","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"import json\nimport os\nimport shutil\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nimport kagglehub                              # pre-installed on Kaggle\nimport torch\nfrom datasets import Dataset, DatasetDict\nfrom peft import LoraConfig, get_peft_model, prepare_model_for_kbit_training\nfrom transformers import (\n    AutoModelForCausalLM,\n    AutoProcessor,                            # ← Gemma 4 uses AutoProcessor (multimodal)\n    BitsAndBytesConfig,\n)\nfrom trl import SFTConfig, SFTTrainer\n\nprint(f\"PyTorch     : {torch.__version__}\")\nprint(f\"CUDA        : {torch.cuda.is_available()}\")\nif torch.cuda.is_available():\n    for i in range(torch.cuda.device_count()):\n        props = torch.cuda.get_device_properties(i)\n        print(f\"  GPU {i}     : {props.name}  ({props.total_memory / 1e9:.1f} GB)\")\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-13T10:46:49.724137Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-13T10:46:49.724410Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-13T10:47:18.963734Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-13T10:46:49.724388Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-13T10:47:18.962940Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"PyTorch     : 2.10.0+cu128\nCUDA        : True\n  GPU 0     : Tesla T4  (15.6 GB)\n  GPU 1     : Tesla T4  (15.6 GB)\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":3},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 3. Download Gemma 4 via kagglehub\n\n This uses Kaggle's native model hosting — **no HuggingFace token needed**.\n The model is downloaded to a local path inside the Kaggle environment.\n\n Available variants:\n | Variant | Kaggle path | VRAM (4-bit) |\n |---------|-------------|-------------|\n | E4B (~4B) | `google/gemma-4/transformers/gemma-4-e4b` | ~6 GB |\n | 12B | `google/gemma-4/transformers/gemma-4-12b` | ~10 GB |\n | 27B | `google/gemma-4/transformers/gemma-4-27b` | ~18 GB |\n\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"\n# ─── Choose your model variant ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n# For Kaggle T4 (16 GB VRAM) with QLoRA 4-bit, both E4B and 12B work.\n# 12B gives better summarization quality; E4B trains faster.\n\nKAGGLE_MODEL_HANDLE = \"google/gemma-4/transformers/gemma-4-e4b\"   # ← change to gemma-4-e4b for smaller\n\nprint(f\"⬇  Downloading model: {KAGGLE_MODEL_HANDLE}\")\nMODEL_PATH = kagglehub.model_download(KAGGLE_MODEL_HANDLE)\nprint(f\"✅ Model path: {MODEL_PATH}\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-13T10:47:18.965162Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-13T10:47:18.965845Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-13T10:47:19.261268Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-13T10:47:18.965761Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-13T10:47:19.260649Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"⬇  Downloading model: google/gemma-4/transformers/gemma-4-e4b\n✅ Model path: /kaggle/input/models/google/gemma-4/transformers/gemma-4-e4b/1\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":4},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 4. Configuration","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"OUTPUT_DIR  = \"/kaggle/working/checkpoints\"\nADAPTER_DIR = \"/kaggle/working/checkpoints/final_adapter\"\n\n# ── Training hyperparameters (tuned for T4 16 GB + 12B QLoRA) ────────────────\nLORA_R       = 16\nLORA_ALPHA   = 32\nLORA_DROPOUT = 0.05\nMAX_SEQ_LEN  = 512\nBATCH_SIZE   = 1     # 1 for 12B; use 2 for E4B\nGRAD_ACCUM   = 16     # effective batch = 16 (or 8 for E4B)\nLR           = 2e-4\nEPOCHS       = 3\n\n# ── Prompt templates (text-only — Gemma 4 text summarization) ─────────────────\nSTYLE_TEMPLATES = {\n    \"short\": (\n        \"You are an expert AI news summarizer. \"\n        \"Write a concise 2–3 sentence summary of the following article. \"\n        \"Preserve key entities, dates, and findings.\\n\\nArticle:\\n{article}\\n\\nSummary:\"\n    ),\n    \"bullet\": (\n        \"You are an expert AI news summarizer. \"\n        \"Extract the 4–6 most important points from the article as concise bullet points.\\n\\n\"\n        \"Article:\\n{article}\\n\\nKey Points:\"\n    ),\n    \"headline\": (\n        \"You are an expert AI news editor. \"\n        \"First write a punchy headline, then write a 2-sentence summary.\\n\\n\"\n        \"Article:\\n{article}\\n\\nHeadline and Summary:\"\n    ),\n    \"detailed\": (\n        \"You are an expert AI news analyst. \"\n        \"Provide a detailed structured summary with: \"\n        \"1) Headline 2) Main Summary (3–4 sentences) \"\n        \"3) Key Points (bullet list) 4) Takeaway (one sentence).\\n\\n\"\n        \"Article:\\n{article}\\n\\nStructured Summary:\"\n    ),\n}\n\nCHAT_TEMPLATE = (\n    \"<start_of_turn>user\\n{prompt}<end_of_turn>\\n\"\n    \"<start_of_turn>model\\n{response}<end_of_turn>\"\n)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-13T10:47:19.262153Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-13T10:47:19.262582Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-13T10:47:19.267928Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-13T10:47:19.262556Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-13T10:47:19.267266Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":5},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 5. Load Processor (Tokenizer for Gemma 4)\nGemma 4 is a multimodal model, so it uses `AutoProcessor` instead of\n`AutoTokenizer`. For text-only summarization it works identically —\njust call `processor(text, ...)` instead of `tokenizer(text, ...)`.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"print(\"Loading processor (tokenizer) from local model path …\")\nprocessor = AutoProcessor.from_pretrained(MODEL_PATH)\n\n# For SFT we need the underlying tokenizer\ntokenizer = processor.tokenizer if hasattr(processor, \"tokenizer\") else processor\n\nif tokenizer.pad_token is None:\n    tokenizer.pad_token = tokenizer.eos_token\ntokenizer.padding_side = \"right\"   # required for SFT loss masking\n\nprint(f\"✅ Vocab size   : {tokenizer.vocab_size:,}\")\nprint(f\"   Pad token   : {tokenizer.pad_token!r}\")\nprint(f\"   EOS token   : {tokenizer.eos_token!r}\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-13T10:47:19.269549Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-13T10:47:19.269915Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-13T10:47:22.582243Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-13T10:47:19.269890Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-13T10:47:22.581579Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Loading processor (tokenizer) from local model path …\n✅ Vocab size   : 262,144\n   Pad token   : '<pad>'\n   EOS token   : '<eos>'\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":6},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 6. Load Dataset\n\n **Option A** — Upload your prepared JSONL files as a Kaggle Dataset named `gemma-news-data`\n and attach it to this notebook (Add-ons → Datasets).\n\n **Option B** — Upload `data/sample_dataset.jsonl` directly to `/kaggle/input/`.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"def load_jsonl(path: str) -> list[dict]:\n    records = []\n    with open(path, encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        for line in f:\n            line = line.strip()\n            if line:\n                records.append(json.loads(line))\n    return records\n\n\ndef build_target(record: dict) -> str:\n    style      = record.get(\"style\", \"detailed\")\n    summary    = record.get(\"summary\", \"\")\n    headline   = record.get(\"headline\", \"\")\n    key_points = record.get(\"key_points\", [])\n\n    if style == \"short\":\n        return summary\n    if style == \"bullet\":\n        pts = key_points or [s.strip() for s in summary.split(\".\") if s.strip()]\n        return \"\\n\".join(f\"• {p}\" for p in pts[:5])\n    if style == \"headline\":\n        return f\"**{headline}**\\n\\n{summary}\" if headline else summary\n\n    # detailed\n    parts = []\n    if headline:   parts.append(f\"**Headline:** {headline}\")\n    if summary:    parts.append(f\"\\n**Summary:** {summary}\")\n    if key_points:\n        pts = \"\\n\".join(f\"• {p}\" for p in key_points)\n        parts.append(f\"\\n**Key Points:**\\n{pts}\")\n    takeaway = key_points[-1] if key_points else \"\"\n    if takeaway:   parts.append(f\"\\n**Takeaway:** {takeaway}\")\n    return \"\\n\".join(parts)\n\n\ndef format_record(record: dict) -> dict:\n    style  = record.get(\"style\", \"detailed\")\n    prompt = STYLE_TEMPLATES[style].format(article=record[\"article\"].strip())\n    target = build_target(record)\n    text   = CHAT_TEMPLATE.format(prompt=prompt, response=target)\n    return {\"text\": text}\n\n\n# ── Resolve dataset paths ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nTRAIN_FILE = \"/kaggle/input/datasets/deetyam/gemma-news-data/train.jsonl\"\nVAL_FILE   = \"/kaggle/input/datasets/deetyam/gemma-news-data/val.jsonl\"\n\n# Fallback: use the 50-record sample shipped in this repo\nif not Path(TRAIN_FILE).exists():\n    print(\"⚠ Processed splits not found — falling back to sample_dataset.jsonl\")\n    # Copy the sample from the repo dataset if attached\n    TRAIN_FILE = \"/kaggle/input/gemma-news-summarizer/data/sample_dataset.jsonl\"\n    VAL_FILE   = None\n\ntrain_records = load_jsonl(TRAIN_FILE)\nval_records   = load_jsonl(VAL_FILE) if VAL_FILE and Path(VAL_FILE).exists() else train_records[:10]\n\ntrain_data = [format_record(r) for r in train_records]\nval_data   = [format_record(r) for r in val_records]\n\nds = DatasetDict({\n    \"train\":      Dataset.from_list(train_data),\n    \"validation\": Dataset.from_list(val_data),\n})\n\nprint(f\"\\nDataset loaded:\")\nprint(f\"  Train : {len(ds['train'])} examples\")\nprint(f\"  Val   : {len(ds['validation'])} examples\")\nprint(f\"\\nSample prompt (first 400 chars):\")\nprint(ds[\"train\"][0][\"text\"][:400])","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-13T10:47:22.583130Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-13T10:47:22.583423Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-13T10:47:22.916614Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-13T10:47:22.583389Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-13T10:47:22.915877Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"\nDataset loaded:\n  Train : 3592 examples\n  Val   : 449 examples\n\nSample prompt (first 400 chars):\n<start_of_turn>user\nYou are an expert AI news analyst. Provide a detailed structured summary with: 1) Headline 2) Main Summary (3–4 sentences) 3) Key Points (bullet list) 4) Takeaway (one sentence).\n\nArticle:\nThe foursome of chirpy college students warmed up in the River Ridge course tee box, focusing on loosening their legs before taking their first shot on a par-four hole. Cody Seybold ran towar\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":7},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 7. Load Base Model in 4-bit (QLoRA)","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"bnb_config = BitsAndBytesConfig(\n    load_in_4bit=True,\n    bnb_4bit_quant_type=\"nf4\",\n    bnb_4bit_compute_dtype=torch.bfloat16,\n    bnb_4bit_use_double_quant=True,   # nested quantisation saves ~0.4 GB extra\n)\n\nprint(f\"Loading model from: {MODEL_PATH}\")\nprint(\"(Using 4-bit NF4 quantisation + double quantisation)\")\n\n# Example: Map multimodal towers to CPU\n# 1. Simplify the device_map to only use the GPU\ndevice_map = {\"\": 0} \n\n# 2. Update the loading call\nmodel = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(\n    MODEL_PATH,\n    quantization_config=bnb_config,\n    device_map=device_map, # Forces everything onto the GPU\n    torch_dtype=torch.bfloat16,\n)\n\nprint(f\"\\nModel memory footprint : {model.get_memory_footprint() / 1e9:.2f} GB\")\n# 1. Clear existing memory first\nimport gc\nimport torch\nfrom peft import get_peft_model, LoraConfig\n\n# 1. Clear existing memory\ngc.collect()\ntorch.cuda.empty_cache()\n\n# 2. Instead of prepare_model_for_kbit_training, enable gradient checkpointing directly\nmodel.config.use_cache = False\nmodel.gradient_checkpointing_enable()\n\n# 3. Proceed directly to applying LoRA (Cell 8)\nprint(\"Gradient checkpointing enabled. You can now proceed to apply LoRA adapters.\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-13T10:47:22.917732Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-13T10:47:22.918135Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stderr","text":"[transformers] `torch_dtype` is deprecated! Use `dtype` instead!\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"Loading model from: /kaggle/input/models/google/gemma-4/transformers/gemma-4-e4b/1\n(Using 4-bit NF4 quantisation + double quantisation)\n","output_type":"stream"},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"Loading weights:   0%|          | 0/2076 [00:00<?, ?it/s]","application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json":{"version_major":2,"version_minor":0,"model_id":"f416f30289624aa19891ab62b26aa4eb"}},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":" ## 8. Apply LoRA Adapters","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"lora_config = LoraConfig(\n    r=LORA_R,\n    lora_alpha=LORA_ALPHA,\n    # Gemma 4 uses same attention projection names as Gemma 3\n    target_modules=[\"linear\"],\n    lora_dropout=LORA_DROPOUT,\n    bias=\"none\",\n    task_type=\"CAUSAL_LM\",\n)\n\nmodel = get_peft_model(model, lora_config)\nmodel.print_trainable_parameters()\n# Expected: ~0.5–1% of total params for r=16","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 9. Train","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"training_args = SFTConfig(\n    output_dir=OUTPUT_DIR,\n    num_train_epochs=EPOCHS,\n    per_device_train_batch_size=BATCH_SIZE,\n    per_device_eval_batch_size=BATCH_SIZE,\n    gradient_accumulation_steps=GRAD_ACCUM,\n    learning_rate=LR,\n    weight_decay=0.01,\n    warmup_ratio=0.03,\n    lr_scheduler_type=\n    \"cosine\",\n    max_grad_norm=0.3,\n    logging_steps=10,\n    eval_steps=50,\n    save_steps=50,\n    save_total_limit=2,\n    load_best_model_at_end=True,\n    metric_for_best_model=\"eval_loss\",\n    eval_strategy=\"steps\",\n    bf16=True,\n    gradient_checkpointing=True,\n    report_to=\"none\",              # set \"wandb\" if you have W&B\n    max_length=MAX_SEQ_LEN,\n    dataset_text_field=\"text\",\n    packing=False,\n    optim=\"paged_adamw_8bit\",     # memory-efficient for QLoRA\n)\n\ntrainer = SFTTrainer(\n    model=model,\n    #tokenizer=tokenizer,\n    train_dataset=ds[\"train\"],\n    eval_dataset=ds[\"validation\"],\n    args=training_args,\n    #max_seq_length=MAX_SEQ_LEN,\n    processing_class=tokenizer,\n)\n\nprint(\"🚀 Starting training …\")\nprint(f\"   Epochs          : {EPOCHS}\")\nprint(f\"   Effective batch : {BATCH_SIZE * GRAD_ACCUM}\")\nprint(f\"   Learning rate   : {LR}\")\nprint(f\"   Max seq length  : {MAX_SEQ_LEN}\")\n\ntrainer.train()","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 10. Save LoRA Adapter","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"Path(ADAPTER_DIR).mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\ntrainer.model.save_pretrained(ADAPTER_DIR)\ntokenizer.save_pretrained(ADAPTER_DIR)\n\n# Also save the processor (needed for inference)\nprocessor.save_pretrained(ADAPTER_DIR)\n\nprint(f\"✅ Adapter saved to: {ADAPTER_DIR}\")\nprint(f\"   Contents: {list(Path(ADAPTER_DIR).iterdir())}\")","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 11. Quick Inference Test (verify the adapter works)","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"from peft import PeftModel\n\n# Reload base model (merge adapter for faster inference)\nprint(\"Reloading base for inference test …\")\nbase_infer = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(\n    MODEL_PATH,\n    torch_dtype=torch.bfloat16,\n    device_map=\"auto\",\n)\nmodel_merged = PeftModel.from_pretrained(base_infer, ADAPTER_DIR)\nmodel_merged = model_merged.merge_and_unload()\nmodel_merged.eval()\n\n# ── Run a test summary ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nTEST_ARTICLE = \"\"\"\nGoogle DeepMind released Gemini Ultra 2, claiming it surpasses GPT-5 on every major benchmark\nincluding MMLU, HumanEval, and MATH. The new model features a 4 million token context window\nand native multimodal processing across text, image, audio, and video. It will be available\nthrough Gemini Advanced subscriptions starting next month at no extra cost for current users.\n\"\"\"\n\nprompt    = STYLE_TEMPLATES[\"detailed\"].format(article=TEST_ARTICLE)\nchat_msgs = [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}]\n\n# Use apply_chat_template from the tokenizer\nformatted = tokenizer.apply_chat_template(\n    chat_msgs, tokenize=False, add_generation_prompt=True\n)\n\ninputs = tokenizer(formatted, return_tensors=\"pt\").to(model_merged.device)\nprompt_len = inputs[\"input_ids\"].shape[1]\n\nwith torch.inference_mode():\n    output_ids = model_merged.generate(\n        **inputs,\n        max_new_tokens=400,\n        temperature=0.7,\n        do_sample=True,\n        repetition_penalty=1.1,\n        pad_token_id=tokenizer.pad_token_id,\n        eos_token_id=tokenizer.eos_token_id,\n    )\n\ngenerated = tokenizer.decode(output_ids[0][prompt_len:], skip_special_tokens=True)\nprint(\"─\" * 60)\nprint(\"GENERATED SUMMARY:\")\nprint(\"─\" * 60)\nprint(generated)","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 12. Zip & Download the Adapter\n\nAfter running this cell, go to the **Output** panel (right side) and\ndownload `final_adapter.zip`.\n\nThen on your local machine, extract it to `checkpoints/final_adapter/`.\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"zip_path = \"/kaggle/working/final_adapter\"\nshutil.make_archive(zip_path, \"zip\", ADAPTER_DIR)\nprint(f\"✅ Zipped: {zip_path}.zip\")\nprint()\nprint(\"Next steps:\")\nprint(\"  1. Download final_adapter.zip from the Kaggle Output panel\")\nprint(\"  2. Extract it on your machine:\")\nprint(\"     unzip final_adapter.zip -d checkpoints/final_adapter/\")\nprint(\"  3. Start the API:\")\nprint(\"     uvicorn api.main:app --reload\")\nprint(\"  4. Open the frontend:\")\nprint(\"     cd frontend && npm run dev\")\n","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null}]}